text: Colobothea varia is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Johan Christian Fabricius in 1787. It is known from Venezuela, Panama, and French Guiana.BioLib.cz - Colobothea varia. Retrieved 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Colobotheini Category:Beetles described in 1787
